        "id": 2688455,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-08-02T00:02:17.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Our discussion in the recent purchases thread reminded me I promised to post my note on the 1993 Bertheau Amoureuses:</p>\n<p>This perfectly preserved bottle of the 1993 Chambolle-Musigny 1er Cru Les Amoureuses soars from the glass with a glorious bouquet of raspberries, dried rose petals, Egyptian musk, candied peel and grilled squab, complemented by an elusive top-note of violets. On the palate, it\u2019s medium to full-bodied, satiny and enveloping, the vintage\u2019s crisp spine of acidity beautifully cloaked in elegantly degraded fruit, its tannins melting and its finish long and pungently floral.</p>\n<p>This year I also picked up a 1972 Bonnes-Mares and 1976 Chambolle AOC so I\u2019m on a bit of a Bertheau kick\u2026</p>",
